  "local_port": 44292,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some useful websites for students?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here\u2019s a list of **useful websites for students**, categorized by their primary functions. These resources can help with studying, research, organization, writing, and more.\n\n---\n\n### **1. **Online Learning & Course Materials**\n- **[Khan Academy](https://www.khanacademy.org/):**\n  - Offers free courses on a wide range of subjects, including math, science, economics, and humanities.\n- **[Coursera](https://www.coursera.org/):**\n  - Provides access to courses from top universities and institutions. Some courses are free, while others require payment or offer certificates.\n- **[edX](https://www.edx.org/):**\n  - Similar to Coursera, offering courses from universities worldwide. Many courses are free to audit.\n\n### **2. **Study Aids & Practice**\n- **[Quizlet](https://quizlet.com/):**\n  - Create and study flashcards, join study sets created by others, and use various study modes like games and tests.\n- **[Chegg](https://www.chegg.com/):**\n  - Offers textbook rentals, homework help, and tutoring services. Note that some services require a subscription.\n- **[Wolfram Alpha](https://www.wolframalpha.com/):**\n  - A computational engine useful for solving math problems, generating data, and exploring various academic topics.\n\n### **3. **Research & Reference**\n- **[Google Scholar](https://scholar.google.com/):**\n  - Search for scholarly articles, theses, books, and conference papers across various disciplines.\n- **[JSTOR](https://www.jstor.org/):**\n  - Provides access to thousands of academic journals, books, and primary sources. Some content is free, while full access may require a subscription or institutional login.\n- **[PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/):**\n  - A free resource for finding biomedical and life sciences literature.\n\n### **4. **Writing & Citation**\n- **[Grammarly](https://www.grammarly.com/):**\n  - An online writing assistant that helps with grammar, punctuation, style, and plagiarism checks.\n- **[Purdue Online Writing Lab (OWL)](https://owl.purdue.edu/):**\n  - Offers comprehensive guides on writing, research, citation styles (APA, MLA, Chicago), and more.\n- **[Zotero](https://www.zotero.org/):**\n  - A free reference manager that helps collect, organize, cite, and share research sources.\n\n### **5. **Productivity & Organization**\n- **[Trello](https://trello.com/):**\n  - A project management tool that uses boards, lists, and cards to help organize tasks and collaborate with others.\n- **[Notion](https://www.notion.so/):**\n  - An all-in-one workspace for note-taking, project management, and organization.\n- **[Microsoft OneNote](https://www.onenote.com/):**\n  - A digital notebook for organizing notes, assignments, and research.\n\n### **6. **Libraries & eBooks**\n- **[Project Gutenberg](https://www.gutenberg.org/):**\n  - Offers over 60,000 free eBooks, including many classic works.\n- **[Internet Archive](https://archive.org/):**\n  - A vast digital library with free books, movies, software, music, and more.\n\n### **7. **Career & Internships**\n- **[LinkedIn Learning](https://www.linkedin.com/learning/):**\n  - Provides video courses on a wide range of professional skills. Access may require a subscription.\n- **[Handshake](https://joinhandshake.com/):**\n  - A platform connecting students with employers for internships, jobs, and career events.\n\n### **8. **Specialized Tools**\n- **[Wolfram Alpha](https://www.wolframalpha.com/):**\n  - A powerful computational engine for mathematics, data analysis, and more.\n- **[Desmos](https://www.desmos.com/):**\n  - An advanced graphing calculator implemented as a web application, useful for visualizing math problems.\n- **[Canva](https://www.canva.com/):**\n  - An easy-to-use graphic design tool for creating presentations, posters, infographics, and other visual content.\n\n### **9. **Language Learning**\n- **[Duolingo](https://www.duolingo.com/):**\n  - A free platform for learning multiple languages through interactive exercises.\n- **[Memrise](https://www.memrise.com/):**\n  - Offers courses in various languages with a focus on vocabulary and phrases through spaced repetition.\n\n### **10. **Mental Health & Wellbeing**\n- **[Headspace](https://www.headspace.com/):**\n  - Provides guided meditation and mindfulness exercises to help manage stress and improve focus. Subscription-based.\n- **[Calm](https://www.calm.com/):**\n  - Another app offering meditation, sleep stories, and relaxation techniques. Subscription-based.\n\n---\n\nThese websites cater to a variety of student needs, from academic support and research to organization and personal development. Depending on your specific requirements, you might find one or several of these resources particularly beneficial. Always check if your school or institution provides free access to some of these services, as many educational institutions have subscriptions or partnerships that can grant you additional benefits.",
